OL,3,CDeadly European heatwave claims
OL,4,Chundreds of lives as temperatures soar
OL,6,FEurope is the world's fastest-warming
OL,7,Fcontinent, with temperatures
OL,8,Fincreasing twice as fast as the global
OL,9,Faverage since the 1980s, according to
OL,10,Fthe European Union's Copernicus
OL,11,FClimate Change Service.
OL,13,FFrance introduced several extreme
OL,14,Ftemperature measures after a heatwave
OL,15,Fin 2003 caused nearly 15,000 excess
OL,16,Fdeaths, with the elderly the hardest
OL,17,Fhit.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
